<p class="">I have no doubt that the Attorney-General will reply to this point later, but my reading of itâ€”and I think it is accurateâ€”is that the person would have to be a "citizen" of New Zealand before he could be accepted here as a British subject. If, instead, he is a "British subject in New Zealand" he would not be recognised as a British subject here. I agree with the -view put forward in certain quartersâ€”</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
